The paper focuses on a technique for improving the efficiency of Mutation Based Fault Localisation (MBFL) techniques, which are commonly used in software engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also involves statistical inference and machine learning techniques, which suggest possible categories of cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with fault localisation in software systems, which could fall under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
